.:: Puzzle 6x3-Level-8-2::.
There are 3 different favourite beverages: soy-milk, fanta, juice
The people have 3 different jobs:  dancer, manager, writer
The people grow 3 different varities of flowers: rose, daffodil, dahlia
3 different games are played: go, whist, mah-jongg
House: victorian, tower, art-deco
There are 3 different favourite colors: emerald, ivory, aquamarine
 1. the person who growsrose is not to the right of the person drinking fanta##8
 2. the person playing whist is the person who likes ivory##1
 3. the person drinking fanta is the person who growsdaffodil##1
 4. the writer is not to the left of the person drinking fanta##8
 5. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left or right of the dancer##3
 6. the writer is on the right of the dancer##1
 7. the person who likes ivory is on the left of the person drinking soy-milk##1
 8. the victorian house is on the far left##1
 9. the person playing whist is not the person who growsrose##6
10. the person who growsdaffodil is somewhere to the right of the victorian house##5
11. the person playing whist is not to the right of the person playing go##8
12. the person who likes emerald is somewhere to the left of the person who likes ivory##5
13. the person who likes ivory is somewhere between the manager and the art-deco house##7

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |     2      |     3      |
| Beverage         | juice | fanta | soy-milk |
| Job           | manager     | dancer     | writer     |
| Flower   | rose       | daffodil      | dahlia     |
